<node id="Luật">
  <data key="d0">Luật</data>
  <data key="d1">QUYỀN_NGHĨA_VỤ</data>
  <data key="d2">Luật is a comprehensive legal framework in Vietnam that governs various aspects of business operations, rights, and responsibilities. It defines the rights and obligations of enterprises, their owners, and the state, ensuring that all parties are governed by established rules and regulations. This legal framework covers the rights and responsibilities of members within a company, including the procedures for maintaining the Sổ Đăng Ký Thành Viên, which is the register of company members. Additionally, Luật regulates the operations and meetings of the company's governing body, ensuring that all activities are conducted in accordance with legal standards.

Luật also governs the naming of businesses, setting out regulations on prohibited names and overlapping names to prevent confusion and protect the interests of all parties. It addresses the regulation of gender transition and the protection of personal privacy, indicating its broad scope in safeguarding individual rights. In the context of enterprises providing public interest products and services, Luật specifies the rights and obligations of such enterprises and social enterprises, ensuring they operate in a manner that benefits the public and adheres to legal requirements.

Furthermore, Luật encompasses the legal framework governing the operations and regulations of corporations, including provisions for reducing registered capital, the repurchase and payment of shares, and the conditions under which shares can be transferred. It also regulates the roles within a company, the rights and obligations of shareholders, and the responsibilities of companies towards the state and their members. Additionally, Luật provides specific regulations for the qualifications and conditions of board members, including those for state-owned enterprises, and outlines the standards and conditions for the position of Kiểm soát viên.

Overall, Luật serves as a comprehensive legal framework that supports the efficient and lawful operation of businesses and protects the rights of individuals and entities within the Vietnamese legal system.&lt;SEP&gt;The law refers to the legal framework that governs the registration and operation of private enterprises and economic groups.&lt;SEP&gt;Luật refers to the legal regulations that govern the actions and responsibilities of parent and subsidiary companies.&lt;SEP&gt;Luật refers to the law that governs the rights and obligations of the members in the company.&lt;SEP&gt;Luật refers to the law that contains the regulations and provisions for the establishment and operation of businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Luật refers to the legal framework governing the procedures for enforcing and challenging arbitration decisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846633705870effa2d882763f1693f90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-902fe4ca615a8ea2fb07c3876622d200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-870356636a26bb390c46554c34ceb657&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fce2849b8973f1a159252908a132579a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c4083a7e93b6ad10b316c67434aca7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d52676760b287e9164a8b2a57de3d57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0941ba0e34f54b5fcc1460ed44a10cff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d99794c741473468cfbf38d98973119&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd21806392f264f4bbe4bbe4d4c4686a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33f981a65016c41f688ba0ac17a35ac7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-705217d07d78fdf7f9b9f642d9c62131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afb6321b2b86d4ca9f69b3b408f671a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-181537e875bd1f5ba6572b043272e618&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-643d72cdd6873e78e2d39abbf824c8bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af079df7102c58f84652bfeb21c7a17a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c9b32b2b806556ed1dd36c13de6e313&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-444a844ae4151849d71498d312b5d52d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65e07d9d273b5f52fb62308b1cffe434&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-952bef1a1bafd78690b17fd797f3d33e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8bb762ad781038843f3cf2f3790105d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-925f6a057b7d8e551fd4f47576508ca0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45f4215d40e0caccca1eaa62a7f0ec73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d59be88d8f39c9fce708d8b3f0c8014&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b12f2587388d6a4e9e558de512dc2860&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-111878a66be557377de6fec57d456ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45f9f1328d58ac04c74cf2a1422490ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c9e86e115e2f87b380e003f8d31484e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773853801</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quyền Nhân Thân">
  <data key="d0">Quyền Nhân Thân</data>
  <data key="d1">QUYỀN_NGHĨA_VỤ</data>
  <data key="d2">Quyền nhân thân refers to personal rights that are aligned with the gender an individual has transitioned to, as regulated by the law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846633705870effa2d882763f1693f90</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773848981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hợp Đồng">
  <data key="d0">Hợp Đồng</data>
  <data key="d1">QUYỀN_NGHĨA_VỤ</data>
  <data key="d2">Hợp Đồng refers to a legal agreement that establishes the terms and conditions between parties. It can include various elements such as the subject, quantity, quality, price, payment method, performance period, location, execution method, rights and obligations of the parties, liability for breach, and dispute resolution methods. Hợp Đồng is a mutual agreement that can be used to establish, change, or terminate civil rights and obligations. It is commonly used in transactions between a buyer and a seller, where the buyer has the right to cancel the contract if the seller fails to fulfill their obligations. Additionally, Hợp Đồng can also refer to a lease agreement that outlines the rights and obligations of both the tenant and the landlord, including the terms of the lease and the conditions for termination. Parties involved in a Hợp Đồng are not allowed to disclose personal or family secrets learned during the contract process without mutual agreement. The applicable law for a Hợp Đồng is determined by the law of the country with the closest connection to the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracts between the company and its owner or related individuals must be recorded and kept as a separate file of the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846633705870effa2d882763f1693f90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e4f3de95acd7468b8d781714a57816a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-260bea9c64a292b86aedaae3fb25a8dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7c9b850c56df03c6a0092f33eddd51c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b76bceedbe3231fcd1a7081ac9ec062b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb0e6ef087a638bbb3f5e1626539a69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce15824853c084575e7d85b3e8d79015&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0cda21c37a8b4d265d1fff1cf5f7aea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-823e07d4a480b69d7f6ec00924cb4793</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773851979</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quan Hệ Dân Sự">
  <data key="d0">Quan Hệ Dân Sự</data>
  <data key="d1">QUYỀN_NGHĨA_VỤ</data>
  <data key="d2">Quan hệ dân sự refers to civil relationships where changes in residence must be communicated to the other party if it affects rights and obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846633705870effa2d882763f1693f90</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773848981</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pháp Nhân">
  <data key="d0">Pháp Nhân</data>
  <data key="d1">CHỦ_THỂ</data>
  <data key="d2">Pháp Nhân refers to legal entities that can act as guardians and must meet certain conditions to do so.&lt;SEP&gt;Pháp Nhân is a legal entity that must have a charter, a name in Vietnamese, a headquarters, and other organizational structures as defined by the law.&lt;SEP&gt;Pháp Nhân refers to legal entities that can be transformed into different forms, dissolved, or declared bankrupt according to the regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Pháp Nhân is a legal entity established by the state and is not responsible for civil obligations arising from the state's civil relations.&lt;SEP&gt;Legal entities whose legal status and activities are governed by the laws of the country where they are established.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-651dc401f3963fbef4dfe8d51ab78119&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04c5e255f3522d9b4bfb81a7f18084cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-783bed81f26ddc9c02e87c49f593844b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-514f9934c36c74c2f0599ebba354e5f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-140e730fed36193f2aad721cf39f1907</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773851430</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Người Thân Thích">
  <data key="d0">Người Thân Thích</data>
  <data key="d1">CHỦ_THỂ</data>
  <data key="d2">Người Thân Thích includes individuals such as wife, husband, father, mother, son, daughter, paternal grandfather, paternal grandmother, maternal grandfather, maternal grandmother, full brother, full sister, uncle, aunt, and other close relatives.&lt;SEP&gt;Người Thân Thích refers to close relatives of the person under guardianship who can be chosen as supervisors or make decisions regarding guardianship.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-651dc401f3963fbef4dfe8d51ab78119</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773849023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
