<node id="Người thừa kế">
  <data key="d0">Người thừa kế</data>
  <data key="d1">CHỦ_THỂ</data>
  <data key="d2">Người thừa kế refers to the heirs of a person declared dead. These individuals are designated to inherit assets from the deceased and are named beneficiaries in a will. A Người thừa kế can be a living individual who inherits from the deceased, including those born after the opening of the estate. The heirs have specific rights and obligations regarding the inheritance. In the context of a company, Người thừa kế can also refer to the heirs of a company member who has died, who may take over the work or responsibilities of the deceased member.&lt;SEP&gt;Người thừa kế is the heir or successor who has the right to inherit the name or assets of a former member of the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12ce4f076c1ad11637bf7e2f3ae95048&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c919d97de369bc8d7562186f764b91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47d8802df9ec7324759d67fe67eaf612&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c45985a08d6e2c0940eda170510a01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dbdbb74ad11a83bf1856f95ecdfa309&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd15f05b480bf5c4a3b4b4e068a412cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-651ba86aa84dcd7fdcb6fe6cfa6aacef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7934cedd8a058c40a35091be7e3f1c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45f4215d40e0caccca1eaa62a7f0ec73</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1773853244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
